Fantastic kickoff to the camping season this weekend with old and new friends. Lead a flight of 11 airplanes on an aerial tour of some of the strips the Owens and Panamint valleys have to offer and slept under the stars enjoying a meteor shower. A huge thankyou to @cebury for capturing this footage for me!!! 

#backcountryaviation #aviation #flying
Do you guys think @daherkodiak would take my liver as down payment?

In three weeks I saw Vandy1 in Florida, Kernville and Inyokern. I wonder where I’ll see it next 🤔

#aviation #militaryaviation #jets
Since @bananasssssssss wants to do trailers, here’s my entry for “dirty tires” 😎🤙 thanks @cebury for the drone shots 🔥🔥🔥

Camping under the stars for the meteor shower a few weekends ago with friends. Do me a favor, fly an airplane this week. Even better if you do it with friends. @flyingfiddler and I lead flights on an “aerial tour” of the panamint valley around R2505 showing off some of our favorite off airport strips and ghost towns. My flight of 11 and his flight of 13 then headed up to Independence for ice cream before ending the night camping at one of our favorite spots, “cindercone”. 
Good times with good people
Is there anything else you’d rather be doing?

Beyond excited to share this with you all!!!

It started with and idea and it came to be almost entirely from support of the amazing people I’m grateful to call friends.
To the people I’ve met who can’t satisfy the flying itch with an occasional flight to breakfast. To the people who explore, pioneer, and above all else wish to share that passion with any and all who will listen, this is for you.

Thank you to everyone who gave me pointers and let me bounce ideas off of you at two in the morning. 

Thank you to everyone who takes a second to visit the website and flip through and share the magazine.

Thank you to everyone who submitted one of their awesome stories for me to share.

Thank you.

Make sure tot head over to OffAirportMag.com to check out the current issue and maybe even submit your own story🤘

Time to get back out to the lakebed 🤘
Read about stories like these at offairportmag.com link in bio!!!

My first flight in a tiny plane was a few weeks ago with @bryan_unable in his Cessna 150. We set out at golden hour and took in the sights of the Tehachapi hills speckled with wind turbines. It was an incredible adventure and so fun to document Bryan in flight. Shot with my Pentax 645z with a 55mm 2.8 and Canon 5D mkiii with a 14mm 2.8. 
Contact me for portraits of you doing your awesome thing! ✨
